	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 12:37:38 GMT" name="july2021" type="calendarMonth" >
			<outline text="July 1" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 12:37:39 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="I'm really confused about what's up with archive.org. As I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/06/29.html#a131345&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; on Tuesday, they clearly aren't archiving this blog in any meaningful way. I write this blog with history in mind. I put things here and on the linkblog because I want to be sure historians in the future will find at least one link to this stuff. If archive.org isn't backing it up, that's a big problem. And raises an even bigger question -- what else aren't they archiving? And how do they decide what their priority is? Are they pre-editing history? Or are they trying to be neutral? " created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 12:37:40 GMT" type="outline" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
	</opml>
